Set up a Node.js server using Express framework and connect it to a MySQL database using Sequelize ORM.
Create a React frontend for the login concept with a simple form that includes username and password fields.
Implement server-side validation of the user credentials and authenticate them against the database using Sequelize.
Add Google Sign-in functionality to the login page, using the Google API and a client ID.
Configure the server to handle the Google Sign-in response and create a new user in the database if the user is new, or retrieve the existing user data if the user already exists.
Implement user authentication and session management using JSON Web Tokens (JWT) for secure communication between the client and the server.

npm install @react-oauth/google@latest
